&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fill prescriptions accurately, repackaging donated unit-dose medication into patient vials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage incoming medication orders and select the correct product from our donated inventory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond to patients by phone, text, and email, troubleshooting account or medication questions and guiding them through our tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help patients set up accounts and place orders so they can use our services smoothly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep inventory accurate: remove expired items, update our systems, and reorder supplies like vials and envelopes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pitch in on administrative and operational tasks that keep the pharmacy and patient navigation running.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What makes you a great fit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have 2+ years of pharmacy technician experience in a busy retail setting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re excellent at customer communication across phone, text, and email.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You care about improving access to medication and enjoy working where operations meets people.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re comfortable with pharmacy and CRM software and GSuite, and pick up new tools quickly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re dependable in a full-time, 40-hour, on-site role (Monday to Friday, 9:30am to 6pm).&lt;/li&gt;
